14#ifndef DNS_COMPRESS_H
15#define DNS_COMPRESS_H 1
16
17#include <inttypes.h>
18#include <stdbool.h>
19
20#include <isc/lang.h>
21#include <isc/region.h>
22
23#include <dns/types.h>
24#include <dns/name.h>
25
26ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
27
28/*! \file dns/compress.h
29 * Direct manipulation of the structures is strongly discouraged.
30 *
31 * A name compression context handles compression of multiple DNS names
32 * in relation to a single DNS message. The context can be used to
33 * selectively turn on/off compression for specific names (depending on
34 * the RR type) by using \c dns_compress_setmethods(). Alternately,
35 * compression can be disabled completely using \c
36 * dns_compress_disable().
37 *
38 * \c dns_compress_setmethods() is intended for use by RDATA towire()
39 * implementations, whereas \c dns_compress_disable() is intended to be
40 * used by a nameserver's configuration manager.
41 */
42
43#define DNS_COMPRESS_NONE 0x00 /*%< no compression */
44#define DNS_COMPRESS_GLOBAL14 0x01 /*%< "normal" compression. */
45#define DNS_COMPRESS_ALL 0x01 /*%< all compression. */
46#define DNS_COMPRESS_CASESENSITIVE 0x02 /*%< case sensitive compression. */
47#define DNS_COMPRESS_ENABLED 0x04
48
49/*
50 * DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE must be a power of 2. The compress code
51 * utilizes this assumption.
52 */
53#define DNS_COMPRESS_TABLEBITS 6
54#define DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE (1U << DNS_COMPRESS_TABLEBITS)
55#define DNS_COMPRESS_TABLEMASK (DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE - 1)
56#define DNS_COMPRESS_INITIALNODES 16
57
58typedef struct dns_compressnode dns_compressnode_t;
59
60struct dns_compressnode {
61 dns_compressnode_t *next;
62 uint16_t offset;
63 uint16_t count;
64 isc_region_t r;
65 dns_name_t name;
66};
67
68struct dns_compress {
69 unsigned int magic; /*%< Magic number. */
70 unsigned int allowed; /*%< Allowed methods. */
71 int edns; /*%< Edns version or -1. */
72 /*% Global compression table. */
73 dns_compressnode_t *table[DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE];
74 /*% Preallocated nodes for the table. */
75 dns_compressnode_t initialnodes[DNS_COMPRESS_INITIALNODES];
76 uint16_t count; /*%< Number of nodes. */
77 isc_mem_t *mctx; /*%< Memory context. */
78};
79
80typedef enum {
81 DNS_DECOMPRESS_ANY, /*%< Any compression */
82 DNS_DECOMPRESS_STRICT, /*%< Allowed compression */
83 DNS_DECOMPRESS_NONE /*%< No compression */
84} dns_decompresstype_t;
85
86struct dns_decompress {
87 unsigned int magic; /*%< Magic number. */
88 unsigned int allowed; /*%< Allowed methods. */
89 int edns; /*%< Edns version or -1. */
90 dns_decompresstype_t type; /*%< Strict checking */
91};
92
93isc_result_t
94dns_compress_init(dns_compress_t *cctx, int edns, isc_mem_t *mctx);
95/*%<
96 * Initialise the compression context structure pointed to by
97 * 'cctx'. A freshly initialized context has name compression
98 * enabled, but no methods are set. Please use \c
99 * dns_compress_setmethods() to set a compression method.
100 *
101 * Requires:
102 * \li 'cctx' is a valid dns_compress_t structure.
103 * \li 'mctx' is an initialized memory context.
104 * Ensures:
105 * \li cctx->global is initialized.
106 *
107 * Returns:
108 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
109 */
110
111void
112dns_compress_invalidate(dns_compress_t *cctx);
113
114/*%<
115 * Invalidate the compression structure pointed to by cctx.
116 *
117 * Requires:
118 *\li 'cctx' to be initialized.
119 */
120
121void
122dns_compress_setmethods(dns_compress_t *cctx, unsigned int allowed);
123
124/*%<
125 * Sets allowed compression methods.
126 *
127 * Requires:
128 *\li 'cctx' to be initialized.
129 */
130
131unsigned int
132dns_compress_getmethods(dns_compress_t *cctx);
133
134/*%<
135 * Gets allowed compression methods.
136 *
137 * Requires:
138 *\li 'cctx' to be initialized.
139 *
140 * Returns:
141 *\li allowed compression bitmap.
142 */
143
144void
145dns_compress_disable(dns_compress_t *cctx);
146/*%<
147 * Disables all name compression in the context. Once disabled,
148 * name compression cannot currently be re-enabled.
149 *
150 * Requires:
151 *\li 'cctx' to be initialized.
152 *
153 */
154
155void
156dns_compress_setsensitive(dns_compress_t *cctx, bool sensitive);
157
158/*
159 * Preserve the case of compressed domain names.
160 *
161 * Requires:
162 * 'cctx' to be initialized.
163 */
164
165bool
166dns_compress_getsensitive(dns_compress_t *cctx);
167/*
168 * Return whether case is to be preserved when compressing
169 * domain names.
170 *
171 * Requires:
172 * 'cctx' to be initialized.
173 */
174
175int
176dns_compress_getedns(dns_compress_t *cctx);
177
178/*%<
179 * Gets edns value.
180 *
181 * Requires:
182 *\li 'cctx' to be initialized.
183 *
184 * Returns:
185 *\li -1 .. 255
186 */
187
188bool
189dns_compress_findglobal(dns_compress_t *cctx, const dns_name_t *name,
190 dns_name_t *prefix, uint16_t *offset);
191/*%<
192 * Finds longest possible match of 'name' in the global compression table.
193 *
194 * Requires:
195 *\li 'cctx' to be initialized.
196 *\li 'name' to be a absolute name.
197 *\li 'prefix' to be initialized.
198 *\li 'offset' to point to an uint16_t.
199 *
200 * Ensures:
201 *\li 'prefix' and 'offset' are valid if true is returned.
202 *
203 * Returns:
204 *\li #true / #false
205 */
206
207void
208dns_compress_add(dns_compress_t *cctx, const dns_name_t *name,
209 const dns_name_t *prefix, uint16_t offset);
210/*%<
211 * Add compression pointers for 'name' to the compression table,
212 * not replacing existing pointers.
213 *
214 * Requires:
215 *\li 'cctx' initialized
216 *
217 *\li 'name' must be initialized and absolute, and must remain
218 * valid until the message compression is complete.
219 *
220 *\li 'prefix' must be a prefix returned by
221 * dns_compress_findglobal(), or the same as 'name'.
222 */
223
224void
225dns_compress_rollback(dns_compress_t *cctx, uint16_t offset);
226
227/*%<
228 * Remove any compression pointers from global table >= offset.
229 *
230 * Requires:
231 *\li 'cctx' is initialized.
232 */
233
234void
235dns_decompress_init(dns_decompress_t *dctx, int edns,
236 dns_decompresstype_t type);
237
238/*%<
239 * Initializes 'dctx'.
240 * Records 'edns' and 'type' into the structure.
241 *
242 * Requires:
243 *\li 'dctx' to be a valid pointer.
244 */
245
246void
247dns_decompress_invalidate(dns_decompress_t *dctx);
248
249/*%<
250 * Invalidates 'dctx'.
251 *
252 * Requires:
253 *\li 'dctx' to be initialized
254 */
255
256void
257dns_decompress_setmethods(dns_decompress_t *dctx, unsigned int allowed);
258
259/*%<
260 * Sets 'dctx->allowed' to 'allowed'.
261 *
262 * Requires:
263 *\li 'dctx' to be initialized
264 */
265
266unsigned int
267dns_decompress_getmethods(dns_decompress_t *dctx);
268
269/*%<
270 * Returns 'dctx->allowed'
271 *
272 * Requires:
273 *\li 'dctx' to be initialized
274 */
275
276int
277dns_decompress_edns(dns_decompress_t *dctx);
278
279/*%<
280 * Returns 'dctx->edns'
281 *
282 * Requires:
283 *\li 'dctx' to be initialized
284 */
285
286dns_decompresstype_t
287dns_decompress_type(dns_decompress_t *dctx);
288
289/*%<
290 * Returns 'dctx->type'
291 *
292 * Requires:
293 *\li 'dctx' to be initialized
294 */
295
296ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
297
298#endif /* DNS_COMPRESS_H */
